00:23:13.100 --> 00:23:16.400
The Square Bevel Button was created
specifically on Mac OS X to provide

00:23:16.790 --> 00:23:20.520
for the situation where you want
to have multiple buttons that

00:23:20.520 --> 00:23:22.480
are related that show status.

00:23:22.480 --> 00:23:24.500
The Square Bevel Button does
a really good job of showing

00:23:24.500 --> 00:23:26.060
which one is selected.

00:23:26.060 --> 00:23:28.980
So you have text attributes, you know,
bold, italicized, underlined,

00:23:28.980 --> 00:23:30.390
or alignment or whatever.

00:23:30.430 --> 00:23:32.410
The Bevel Button does
a great job of that.

00:23:32.450 --> 00:23:35.690
The Square Bevel Button also is great
for in the bottom left corner or

00:23:35.690 --> 00:23:38.950
anywhere along the scroll bar edge
of a window because it fits in there.

00:23:38.950 --> 00:23:39.800
It can be any size.

00:23:39.800 --> 00:23:41.730
It can have a pop-up
menu associated with it.

00:23:41.740 --> 00:23:42.810
It can have an icon in it.

00:23:42.930 --> 00:23:44.800
It can have a whole bunch of things.

00:23:44.960 --> 00:23:46.900
It's a great use of it there.

00:23:46.970 --> 00:23:48.220
Great for toolbars, et cetera.

00:23:48.220 --> 00:23:52.240
So this is another way of doing a toolbar
in Mac OS X or doing collections of

00:23:52.240 --> 00:23:54.270
related items that need to show status.

00:23:57.800 --> 00:24:01.360
Another thing on Mac OS X is
the appearance of text.

00:24:01.370 --> 00:24:02.520
It's anti-aliased.

00:24:02.770 --> 00:24:04.700
It's anti-aliased everywhere.

00:24:04.700 --> 00:24:09.340
And the font that's provided through
the system is lucid or grand.

00:24:10.050 --> 00:24:13.220
When you specify a particular
font face in your application,

00:24:13.220 --> 00:24:16.460
when you're drawing text yourself,
you should select text through meta

00:24:16.460 --> 00:24:20.170
font specifications through the
appearance manager for your Carbon.

00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:23.980
Avoid hard coding font references.

00:24:24.390 --> 00:24:26.600
Avoid hard coding font sizes.

00:24:27.020 --> 00:24:30.200
Specifically saying,
"Use Geneva 9 for my interface,"

00:24:30.370 --> 00:24:32.360
is something you should avoid.

00:24:32.440 --> 00:24:35.630
Those fonts may not even
be available in the future.

00:24:36.120 --> 00:24:37.570
Lucida Grande is a system font.

00:24:37.630 --> 00:24:41.000
You need to specify the font that you're
going to use to draw the text on your

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:43.860
interface by using meta specifications.

00:24:43.890 --> 00:24:47.100
Let the system draw it wherever possible.

