00:45:33.950 --> 00:45:35.700
266.

00:45:35.720 --> 00:45:38.000
I don't know what that means.

00:45:38.100 --> 00:45:40.460
So the developer does,
and there must be a reason,

00:45:40.460 --> 00:45:41.560
but you know what?

00:45:41.560 --> 00:45:43.800
The user probably doesn't care.

00:45:43.950 --> 00:45:50.630
So be careful of elevating things
to the primary interface that are

00:45:50.630 --> 00:45:50.630
meaningless to the user in the
context of what they're doing.

00:45:50.920 --> 00:45:52.240
Not only that, we've got something else.

