we still see developers who say, "Ahh."

01:00:24.140 --> 01:00:26.070
Well, I want to give it a different
way of picking colors.

01:00:26.080 --> 01:00:27.920
I've got a better way of picking colors.

01:00:27.940 --> 01:00:30.650
So they choose to offer a
different way of picking colors.

01:00:30.660 --> 01:00:33.240
I don't need to use
the system font picker.

01:00:33.240 --> 01:00:35.980
You know, I don't like it,
or I can't figure out the APIs,

01:00:35.980 --> 01:00:38.200
or I don't know where the APIs are,
or I didn't even know it existed,

01:00:38.300 --> 01:00:39.650
so I wrote my own font picker.

01:00:39.660 --> 01:00:44.140
Well, the problem with that is that users
who come to Mac OS X are going to be

01:00:44.230 --> 01:00:45.480
expecting a consistent experience.

01:00:45.480 --> 01:00:48.460
It's like me looking for a
gas station or a 7-Eleven.

01:00:48.460 --> 01:00:51.900
I want a Coke or a Mountain Dew at
11 o'clock at night,

01:00:51.900 --> 01:00:53.420
and so I say to my wife,
I'm going to go to the 7-Eleven.

01:00:53.560 --> 01:00:54.220
So I go bombing around.

01:00:54.220 --> 01:00:55.840
Well, an hour later,
I still don't have a Coke or

01:00:55.840 --> 01:00:57.280
a Mountain Dew or whatever
it was I wanted to get,

01:00:57.460 --> 01:01:00.560
and I'm still looking for this thing
because the visual cues weren't there.

01:01:00.560 --> 01:01:02.400
The things I was looking
for weren't there.

01:01:04.130 --> 01:01:07.030
If I'm looking to change a
font in all of the applications

01:01:07.030 --> 01:01:09.740
I've ever used on Mac OS X,
do font picking in a certain way,

01:01:09.740 --> 01:01:12.500
and now I get into your application and
your font picking is in a different way,

01:01:12.500 --> 01:01:17.040
it's not that I can't figure it out,
it's that it impedes my productivity.

01:01:17.040 --> 01:01:19.340
It slows me down because
now I'm going to go,

01:01:19.340 --> 01:01:21.910
"Oh,
where do I pick fonts in this product?"

01:01:22.030 --> 01:01:22.880
Where do I choose a color?

01:01:22.970 --> 01:01:23.790
How do I choose a color?

01:01:23.830 --> 01:01:25.500
How does this color picker work?

01:01:25.560 --> 01:01:27.040
We have color pickers on Mac OS X.

01:01:27.040 --> 01:01:28.600
Yes, they're different
between Carbon and Cocoa.

01:01:28.600 --> 01:01:29.160
We know that.

01:01:29.160 --> 01:01:29.740
It's a known bug.

01:01:29.820 --> 01:01:31.300
We're going to fix that.

01:01:31.350 --> 01:01:37.950
That's no excuse to not use the color
picker that's available in the system.

01:01:38.050 --> 01:01:41.900
Because when we do make them the same,
they'll be the same.

01:01:41.900 --> 01:01:41.900
Your application will just offer
color picking the same way that

01:01:41.900 --> 01:01:41.900
every other application does.

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:43.900
Yes, the FOD Picker might not be
available to some of you,

01:01:43.900 --> 01:01:45.780
depending on the
framework that you're in.

01:01:45.830 --> 01:01:46.870
But it will be eventually.

01:01:46.880 --> 01:01:47.970
That's certainly our goal.

01:01:47.980 --> 01:01:49.000
We're investigating that.

01:01:49.000 --> 01:01:53.290
So build your code in
anticipation of it coming.

01:01:54.410 --> 01:01:56.600
Support Unicode in
international customers.

01:01:56.600 --> 01:01:59.160
Mac OS X, I mean,
we made a big message in the keynote,

01:01:59.160 --> 01:02:02.930
in obvious keynote about the
localizability of Mac OS X,

01:02:02.930 --> 01:02:05.340
the multilingual aspects of Mac OS X.

01:02:05.740 --> 01:02:14.130
If you're going to provide a great user
experience for all of your customers,

01:02:14.130 --> 01:02:14.130
which are worldwide, hopefully,
you need to think about all

01:02:14.130 --> 01:02:14.130
the international issues.

01:02:14.900 --> 01:02:17.690
